The name of each benchmark subjects will take you to the subject website. The selection of the benchmark subjects was done based on the area of the polar. The polar charts for the selected six benchmark subjects are in Figure 1.

The alerts generated via the FindBugs v1.3.1 static analysis tool (specifically the FindBugs Eclipse plug-in) were inspected to determine for each alert, if the alert is a true or false positive in the specific subject program. The true positive (TP) and false positive (FP) breakdown are found in Table 2. The alerts generated for each subject and if the alert was determined to be a TP or FP may be found in the following Excel file: SubjectBaselineAlerts.xls.

Subject Downloads

The six subject programs in FaultBench were put into Eclipse projects for evaluation. A clean and changed Eclipse project are provided for each subject program in Table 3. All of the subject programs were run in the standard Eclipse v3.3.1.1 except for iTrust (marked by a *) which was run in Eclipse IDE for Java EE Developers v 3.3.1.1 (this version of Eclipse comes packaged with plug-ins for Web applications). For instructions about how to set up iTrust, please see the iTrust website.
